statements.sql:
select count(*) as aggregate from `inter_entreprises` as `I` inner join `projets` as `P` on `P`.`idProjet` = `I`.`idProjet` inner join `customers` as `C` on `C`.`idCustomer` = `I`.`idEtp` inner join `mdls` as `M` on `M`.`idModule` = `P`.`idModule` left join `modules` as `MD` on `MD`.`idModule` = `M`.`idModule` left join `inters` as `IE` on `IE`.`idProjet` = `P`.`idProjet` left join (SELECT inter_entreprises.idProjet,
SUM(inter_entreprises.nbPlaceReserved) as reserved
FROM inter_entreprises
WHERE inter_entreprises.isActiveInter = 1
GROUP BY inter_entreprises.idProjet) as reservation on `reservation`.`idProjet` = `P`.`idProjet` inner join `ville_codeds` as `VC` on `VC`.`id` = `P`.`idVilleCoded` where `P`.`idCustomer` = 2

select `M`.`module_image` as `moduleLogo`, `IE`.`nbPlace` as `nbPlace`, COALESCE(IE.nbPlace - reservation.reserved, IE.nbPlace) as available, `M`.`moduleName` as `module_name`, `P`.`project_title`, `I`.`nbPlaceReserved`, `C`.`logo` as `etpLogo`, `C`.`customerName`, `I`.`isActiveInter`, `I`.`id`, `C`.`customerEmail` as `customerEmail`, `MD`.`prix` as `totalPrice`, `P`.`dateDebut`, `P`.`dateFin`, `VC`.`ville_name`, `VC`.`vi_code_postal`, `P`.`idProjet`, `C`.`customerPhone`, `P`.`project_reference`, SUBSTR(C.customerName, 1, 1) as initialName, `IE`.`nbPlace` as `nbPlaceTotal` from `inter_entreprises` as `I` inner join `projets` as `P` on `P`.`idProjet` = `I`.`idProjet` inner join `customers` as `C` on `C`.`idCustomer` = `I`.`idEtp` inner join `mdls` as `M` on `M`.`idModule` = `P`.`idModule` left join `modules` as `MD` on `MD`.`idModule` = `M`.`idModule` left join `inters` as `IE` on `IE`.`idProjet` = `P`.`idProjet` left join (SELECT inter_entreprises.idProjet,
SUM(inter_entreprises.nbPlaceReserved) as reserved
FROM inter_entreprises
WHERE inter_entreprises.isActiveInter = 1
GROUP BY inter_entreprises.idProjet) as reservation on `reservation`.`idProjet` = `P`.`idProjet` inner join `ville_codeds` as `VC` on `VC`.`id` = `P`.`idVilleCoded` where `P`.`idCustomer` = 2 order by `I`.`id` desc limit 10 offset 0
select count(*) as aggregate from `inter_entreprises` as `I` inner join `projets` as `P` on `P`.`idProjet` = `I`.`idProjet` where `I`.`isActiveInter` = 1 and `P`.`idCustomer` = 2
select count(*) as aggregate from `inter_entreprises` as `I` inner join `projets` as `P` on `P`.`idProjet` = `I`.`idProjet` where `I`.`isActiveInter` = 2 and `P`.`idCustomer` = 2
select count(*) as aggregate from `inter_entreprises` as `I` inner join `projets` as `P` on `P`.`idProjet` = `I`.`idProjet` where `I`.`isActiveInter` = 3 and `P`.`idCustomer` = 2
select count(*) as aggregate from `inter_entreprises` as `I` inner join `projets` as `P` on `P`.`idProjet` = `I`.`idProjet` where `I`.`isActiveInter` = 0 and `P`.`idCustomer` = 2

select * from `subscriptions` where `subscriptions`.`subscriber_type` = 'App\\Models\\User' and `subscriptions`.`subscriber_id` = 2 and `subscriptions`.`subscriber_id` is not null and `subscriptions`.`deleted_at` is null limit 1
select * from `ville_codeds` as `vc` order by `vc`.`vi_code_postal` asc
select `idLieu`, `li_name`, `ville_name`, `vi_code_postal` from `lieux` inner join `ville_codeds` on `ville_codeds`.`id` = `lieux`.`idVilleCoded` order by `li_name` asc
